JOHANNESBURG – The Gupta-owned Optimum Coal is taking its business rescue practitioners (BRPs) to court. The company's CEO George van der Merwe said the BRPs are incompetent and should be removed. READ: Workers at Optimum coal mine demand payment The rescue practitioners responded, saying Van der Merwe and Oakbay CEO Ronica Ragavan are acting unscrupulously. Optimum is obligated to supply about 400,000 tons of coal to Eskom every month. READ: Mantashe to prioritise reviving Gupta-owned Optimum mine It has not done this since March and the power utility now has to source coal elsewhere at extra cost. Mineworkers went on strike last week over late wages. eNCA